[30;1m1694 | [0m[35m    Create a standard gaussian distribution, which's values never go below[0m
[30;1m1695 | [0m[35m    ``-2.0`` or above ``2.0``. Note that this will lead to small "bumps" of[0m
[30;1m1696 | [0m[35m    higher probability at ``-2.0`` and ``2.0``, as values below/above these[0m
[30;1m1697 | [0m[35m    will be clipped to them. For smoother limitations on gaussian[0m
[30;1m1698 | [0m[35m    distributions, see :class:`TruncatedNormal`.[0m
[30;1m1699 | [0m[35m[0m

[30;1m1463 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m1464 | [0m[35m    This parameter is intended to be used with parameters that would usually[0m
[30;1m1465 | [0m[35m    sample one value per pixel (or one value per pixel and channel). Instead[0m
[30;1m1466 | [0m[35m    of sampling from the other parameter at full resolution, it samples at[0m
[30;1m1467 | [0m[35m    lower resolution, e.g. ``0.5*H x 0.5*W`` with ``H`` being the height and[0m
[30;1m1468 | [0m[35m    ``W`` being the width. After the low-resolution sampling this parameter[0m

[30;1m746 | [0m[35m### Example: Very Complex Augmentation Pipeline[0m
[30;1m747 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m748 | [0m[35mApply a very heavy augmentation pipeline to images (used to create the image [0m
[30;1m749 | [0m[35mat the very top of this readme):[0m

[31m--[ [0m[34mMatch #[0m[33m616[0m[34m of [0m[33m640[0m[31m ]--[0m
   Rule Id: [34mBD000600[0m
       Tag: [34mSecurity.Backdoor.LOLBAS.Windows[0m
  Severity: [36mModerate[0m, Confidence: [36mLow[0m
  Filename: [33m/imgaug-0.4.0/README.md[0m
   Pattern: [32m\s(advpack\.dll|appvlp|at|atbroker|bash|bginfo|bitsadmin|cdb|certutil|cl_invocation\.ps1|cl_mutexverifiers\.ps1|cmd|cmdkey|cmstp|comsvcs\.dll|control|csc|cscript|csi|devtoolslauncher|dfsvc|diskshadow|dnscmd|dnx|dotnet|dxcap|esentutl|eventvwr|excel|expand|extexport|extrac32|findstr|forfiles|ftp|gfxdownloadwrapper|gpscript|hh|ie4uinit|ieadvpack\.dll|ieaframe\.dll|ic|infdefaultinstall|installutil|jsc|makecab|manage-bde\.wsf|mavinject|mftrace|microsoft\.workflow\.compiler|mmc|msbuild|msconfig|msdeploy|msdt|mshta|mshtml\.dll|msc|msxsl|netsh|odbcconf|pcalua|pcwrun|pcwutl\.dll|pester\.bat|powerpnt|presentationhost|pubprn\.vbs|rcsi|reg|regasm|regedit|register-cimprovider|regsvcs|regsvr32|rpcping|rundll32|runonce|runscripthelper|sc|schtasks|scriptrunner|setupapi\.dll|shdocvw\.dll|shell32\.dll|slmgr\.vbs|sqldumper|sqlps|sqltoolsps|squirrel|syncappvpublishingserver|syncappvpublishingserver\.vbs|syssetup\.dll|te|tracker|tttracer|update|url\.dll|verclsid|vsjitdebugger|wab|winrm\.vbs|winword|wmic|wscript|wsl|wsreset|xwizard|zipfldr\.dll)\s[0m
[30;1m727 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m728 | [0m[35m# Pipeline:[0m
[30;1m729 | [0m[35m# (1) Crop images from each side by 1-16px, do not resize the results[0m
[30;1m730 | [0m[35m#     images back to the input size. Keep them at the cropped size.[0m
[30;1m731 | [0m[35m# (2) Horizontally flip 50% of the images.[0m
[30;1m732 | [0m[35m# (3) Blur images using a gaussian kernel with sigma between 0.0 and 3.0.[0m
[30;1m733 | [0m[35mseq = iaa.Sequential([[0m

[31m--[ [0m[34mMatch #[0m[33m617[0m[34m of [0m[33m640[0m[31m ]--[0m

[30;1m1057 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m1058 | [0m[35mWhile the interface is adapted towards re-using instances of augmenters[0m
[30;1m1059 | [0m[35mmany times, you are also free to use them only once. The overhead to[0m
[30;1m1060 | [0m[35minstantiate the augmenters each time is usually negligible.[0m
[30;1m1061 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m1062 | [0m[35m```python[0m
[30;1m1063 | [0m[35mfrom imgaug import augmenters as iaa[0m

[30;1m863 | [0m[35mprint("Points 2", points_aug[1])[0m

[30;1m865 | [0m[35mNote that all coordinates in `imgaug` are subpixel-accurate, which is[0m
[30;1m866 | [0m[35mwhy `x=0.5, y=0.5` denotes the center of the top left pixel.[0m
[30;1m867 | [0m[35m[0m

[30;1m869 | [0m[35m### Example: Augment Images and Bounding Boxes[0m
